     777            8 : // dprint-ignore
     778            8 : export const enum NodeFlags {
     779            8 :     None               = 0,
     780            8 :     Let                = 1 << 0,  // Variable declaration
     781            8 :     Const              = 1 << 1,  // Variable declaration
     782            8 :     Using              = 1 << 2,  // Variable declaration
     783            8 :     AwaitUsing         = Const | Using, // Variable declaration (NOTE: on a single node these flags would otherwise be mutually exclusive)
     784            8 :     NestedNamespace    = 1 << 3,  // Namespace declaration
     785            8 :     Synthesized        = 1 << 4,  // Node was synthesized during transformation
     786            8 :     Namespace          = 1 << 5,  // Namespace declaration
     787            8 :     OptionalChain      = 1 << 6,  // Chained MemberExpression rooted to a pseudo-OptionalExpression
     788            8 :     ExportContext      = 1 << 7,  // Export context (initialized by binding)
     789            8 :     ContainsThis       = 1 << 8,  // Interface contains references to "this"
     790            8 :     HasImplicitReturn  = 1 << 9,  // If function implicitly returns on one of codepaths (initialized by binding)
     791            8 :     HasExplicitReturn  = 1 << 10,  // If function has explicit reachable return on one of codepaths (initialized by binding)
     792            8 :     GlobalAugmentation = 1 << 11,  // Set if module declaration is an augmentation for the global scope
     793            8 :     HasAsyncFunctions  = 1 << 12, // If the file has async functions (initialized by binding)
     794            8 :     DisallowInContext  = 1 << 13, // If node was parsed in a context where 'in-expressions' are not allowed
     795            8 :     YieldContext       = 1 << 14, // If node was parsed in the 'yield' context created when parsing a generator
     796            8 :     DecoratorContext   = 1 << 15, // If node was parsed as part of a decorator
     797            8 :     AwaitContext       = 1 << 16, // If node was parsed in the 'await' context created when parsing an async function
     798            8 :     DisallowConditionalTypesContext = 1 << 17, // If node was parsed in a context where conditional types are not allowed
     799            8 :     ThisNodeHasError   = 1 << 18, // If the parser encountered an error when parsing the code that created this node
     800            8 :     JavaScriptFile     = 1 << 19, // If node was parsed in a JavaScript
     801            8 :     ThisNodeOrAnySubNodesHasError = 1 << 20, // If this node or any of its children had an error
     802            8 :     HasAggregatedChildData = 1 << 21, // If we've computed data from children and cached it in this node
     803            8 : 
     804            8 :     // These flags will be set when the parser encounters a dynamic import expression or 'import.meta' to avoid
     805            8 :     // walking the tree if the flags are not set. However, these flags are just a approximation
     806            8 :     // (hence why it's named "PossiblyContainsDynamicImport") because once set, the flags never get cleared.
     807            8 :     // During editing, if a dynamic import is removed, incremental parsing will *NOT* clear this flag.
     808            8 :     // This means that the tree will always be traversed during module resolution, or when looking for external module indicators.
     809            8 :     // However, the removal operation should not occur often and in the case of the
     810            8 :     // removal, it is likely that users will add the import anyway.
     811            8 :     // The advantage of this approach is its simplicity. For the case of batch compilation,
     812            8 :     // we guarantee that users won't have to pay the price of walking the tree if a dynamic import isn't used.
     813            8 :     /** @internal */ PossiblyContainsDynamicImport = 1 << 22,
     814            8 :     /** @internal */ PossiblyContainsImportMeta    = 1 << 23,
     815            8 : 
     816            8 :     JSDoc                                          = 1 << 24, // If node was parsed inside jsdoc
     817            8 :     /** @internal */ Ambient                       = 1 << 25, // If node was inside an ambient context -- a declaration file, or inside something with the `declare` modifier.
     818            8 :     /** @internal */ InWithStatement               = 1 << 26, // If any ancestor of node was the `statement` of a WithStatement (not the `expression`)
     819            8 :     JsonFile                                       = 1 << 27, // If node was parsed in a Json
     820            8 :     /** @internal */ TypeCached                    = 1 << 28, // If a type was cached for node at any point
     821            8 :     /** @internal */ Deprecated                    = 1 << 29, // If has '@deprecated' JSDoc tag
     822            8 : 
     823            8 :     BlockScoped = Let | Const | Using,
     824            8 :     Constant = Const | Using,
     825            8 : 
     826            8 :     ReachabilityCheckFlags = HasImplicitReturn | HasExplicitReturn,
     827            8 :     ReachabilityAndEmitFlags = ReachabilityCheckFlags | HasAsyncFunctions,
     828            8 : 
     829            8 :     // Parsing context flags
     830            8 :     ContextFlags = DisallowInContext | DisallowConditionalTypesContext | YieldContext | DecoratorContext | AwaitContext | JavaScriptFile | InWithStatement | Ambient,
     831            8 : 
     832            8 :     // Exclude these flags when parsing a Type
     833            8 :     TypeExcludesFlags = YieldContext | AwaitContext,
     834            8 : 
     835            8 :     // Represents all flags that are potentially set once and
     836            8 :     // never cleared on SourceFiles which get re-used in between incremental parses.
     837            8 :     // See the comment above on `PossiblyContainsDynamicImport` and `PossiblyContainsImportMeta`.
     838            8 :     /** @internal */ PermanentlySetIncrementalFlags = PossiblyContainsDynamicImport | PossiblyContainsImportMeta,
     839            8 : 
     840            8 :     // The following flags repurpose other NodeFlags as different meanings for Identifier nodes
     841            8 :     /** @internal */ IdentifierHasExtendedUnicodeEscape = ContainsThis, // Indicates whether the identifier contains an extended unicode escape sequence
     842            8 :     /** @internal */ IdentifierIsInJSDocNamespace = HasAsyncFunctions, // Indicates whether the identifier is part of a JSDoc namespace
     843            8 : }
     844            8 : 
     845            8 : // dprint-ignore
     846            8 : export const enum ModifierFlags {
     847            8 :     None =               0,
     848            8 : 
     849            8 :     // Syntactic/JSDoc modifiers
     850            8 :     Public =             1 << 0,  // Property/Method
     851            8 :     Private =            1 << 1,  // Property/Method
     852            8 :     Protected =          1 << 2,  // Property/Method
     853            8 :     Readonly =           1 << 3,  // Property/Method
     854            8 :     Override =           1 << 4,  // Override method.
     855            8 : 
     856            8 :     // Syntactic-only modifiers
     857            8 :     Export =             1 << 5,  // Declarations
     858            8 :     Abstract =           1 << 6,  // Class/Method/ConstructSignature
     859            8 :     Ambient =            1 << 7,  // Declarations
     860            8 :     Static =             1 << 8,  // Property/Method
     861            8 :     Accessor =           1 << 9,  // Property
     862            8 :     Async =              1 << 10, // Property/Method/Function
     863            8 :     Default =            1 << 11, // Function/Class (export default declaration)
     864            8 :     Const =              1 << 12, // Const enum
     865            8 :     In =                 1 << 13, // Contravariance modifier
     866            8 :     Out =                1 << 14, // Covariance modifier
     867            8 :     Decorator =          1 << 15, // Contains a decorator.
     868            8 : 
     869            8 :     // JSDoc-only modifiers
     870            8 :     Deprecated =         1 << 16, // Deprecated tag.
     871            8 : 
     872            8 :     // Cache-only JSDoc-modifiers. Should match order of Syntactic/JSDoc modifiers, above.
     873            8 :     /** @internal */ JSDocPublic = 1 << 23, // if this value changes, `selectEffectiveModifierFlags` must change accordingly
     874            8 :     /** @internal */ JSDocPrivate = 1 << 24,
     875            8 :     /** @internal */ JSDocProtected = 1 << 25,
     876            8 :     /** @internal */ JSDocReadonly = 1 << 26,
     877            8 :     /** @internal */ JSDocOverride = 1 << 27,
     878            8 : 
     879            8 :     /** @internal */ SyntacticOrJSDocModifiers = Public | Private | Protected | Readonly | Override,
     880            8 :     /** @internal */ SyntacticOnlyModifiers = Export | Ambient | Abstract | Static | Accessor | Async | Default | Const | In | Out | Decorator,
     881            8 :     /** @internal */ SyntacticModifiers = SyntacticOrJSDocModifiers | SyntacticOnlyModifiers,
     882            8 :     /** @internal */ JSDocCacheOnlyModifiers = JSDocPublic | JSDocPrivate | JSDocProtected | JSDocReadonly | JSDocOverride,
     883            8 :     /** @internal */ JSDocOnlyModifiers = Deprecated,
     884            8 :     /** @internal */ NonCacheOnlyModifiers = SyntacticOrJSDocModifiers | SyntacticOnlyModifiers | JSDocOnlyModifiers,
     885            8 : 
     886            8 :     HasComputedJSDocModifiers = 1 << 28, // Indicates the computed modifier flags include modifiers from JSDoc.
     887            8 :     HasComputedFlags =   1 << 29, // Modifier flags have been computed
     888            8 : 
     889            8 :     AccessibilityModifier = Public | Private | Protected,
     890            8 :     // Accessibility modifiers and 'readonly' can be attached to a parameter in a constructor to make it a property.
     891            8 :     ParameterPropertyModifier = AccessibilityModifier | Readonly | Override,
     892            8 :     NonPublicAccessibilityModifier = Private | Protected,
     893            8 : 
     894            8 :     TypeScriptModifier = Ambient | Public | Private | Protected | Readonly | Abstract | Const | Override | In | Out,
     895            8 :     ExportDefault = Export | Default,
     896            8 :     All = Export | Ambient | Public | Private | Protected | Static | Readonly | Abstract | Accessor | Async | Default | Const | Deprecated | Override | In | Out | Decorator,
     897            8 :     Modifier = All & ~Decorator,
     898            8 : }

    1668            8 : // dprint-ignore
    1669            8 : export const enum GeneratedIdentifierFlags {
    1670            8 :     // Kinds
    1671            8 :     None = 0,                           // Not automatically generated.
    1672            8 :     /** @internal */ Auto = 1,             // Automatically generated identifier.
    1673            8 :     /** @internal */ Loop = 2,             // Automatically generated identifier with a preference for '_i'.
    1674            8 :     /** @internal */ Unique = 3,           // Unique name based on the 'text' property.
    1675            8 :     /** @internal */ Node = 4,             // Unique name based on the node in the 'original' property.
    1676            8 :     /** @internal */ KindMask = 7,         // Mask to extract the kind of identifier from its flags.
    1677            8 : 
    1678            8 :     // Flags
    1679            8 :     ReservedInNestedScopes = 1 << 3,    // Reserve the generated name in nested scopes
    1680            8 :     Optimistic = 1 << 4,                // First instance won't use '_#' if there's no conflict
    1681            8 :     FileLevel = 1 << 5,                 // Use only the file identifiers list and not generated names to search for conflicts
    1682            8 :     AllowNameSubstitution = 1 << 6, // Used by `module.ts` to indicate generated nodes which can have substitutions performed upon them (as they were generated by an earlier transform phase)
    1683            8 : }

    2069            8 : export interface MethodSignature extends SignatureDeclarationBase, TypeElement, LocalsContainer {

    2075            8 : 
    2076            8 : // Note that a MethodDeclaration is considered both a ClassElement and an ObjectLiteralElement.
    2077            8 : // Both the grammars for ClassDeclaration and ObjectLiteralExpression allow for MethodDeclarations
    2078            8 : // as child elements, and so a MethodDeclaration satisfies both interfaces.  This avoids the
    2079            8 : // alternative where we would need separate kinds/types for ClassMethodDeclaration and
    2080            8 : // ObjectLiteralMethodDeclaration, which would look identical.
    2081            8 : //
    2082            8 : // Because of this, it may be necessary to determine what sort of MethodDeclaration you have
    2083            8 : // at later stages of the compiler pipeline.  In that case, you can either check the parent kind
    2084            8 : // of the method, or use helpers like isObjectLiteralMethodDeclaration
    2085            8 : export interface MethodDeclaration extends FunctionLikeDeclarationBase, ClassElement, ObjectLiteralElement, JSDocContainer, LocalsContainer, FlowContainer {
    2086            8 :     readonly kind: SyntaxKind.MethodDeclaration;
    2087            8 :     readonly parent: ClassLikeDeclaration | ObjectLiteralExpression;
    2088            8 :     readonly modifiers?: NodeArray<ModifierLike> | undefined;
    2089            8 :     readonly name: PropertyName;
    2090            8 :     readonly body?: FunctionBody | undefined;
    2091            8 : 
    2092            8 :     // The following properties are used only to report grammar errors (see `isGrammarError` in utilities.ts)
    2093            8 :     /** @internal */ readonly exclamationToken?: ExclamationToken | undefined; // A method cannot have an exclamation token
    2094            8 : }
    2095            8 :

    2104            8 :     /** @internal */ readonly type?: TypeNode; // A constructor cannot have a return type annotation
    2105            8 : }

    2364            8 : 
    2365            8 : // Note: 'brands' in our syntax nodes serve to give us a small amount of nominal typing.
    2366            8 : // Consider 'Expression'.  Without the brand, 'Expression' is actually no different
    2367            8 : // (structurally) than 'Node'.  Because of this you can pass any Node to a function that
    2368            8 : // takes an Expression without any error.  By using the 'brands' we ensure that the type
    2369            8 : // checker actually thinks you have something of the right type.  Note: the brands are
    2370            8 : // never actually given values.  At runtime they have zero cost.
    2371            8 : 
    2372            8 : export interface Expression extends Node {
    2373            8 :     _expressionBrand: any;
    2374            8 : }
    2375            8 : 
    2376            8 : export interface OmittedExpression extends Expression {
    2377            8 :     readonly kind: SyntaxKind.OmittedExpression;
    2378            8 : }
    2379            8 :

    2381            8 : // not-emitted node. The 'expression' property of a PartiallyEmittedExpression should be emitted.
    2382            8 : export interface PartiallyEmittedExpression extends LeftHandSideExpression {
    2383            8 :     readonly kind: SyntaxKind.PartiallyEmittedExpression;
    2384            8 :     readonly expression: Expression;

    2738            8 : // The text property of a LiteralExpression stores the interpreted value of the literal in text form. For a StringLiteral,
    2739            8 : // or any literal of a template, this means quotes have been removed and escapes have been converted to actual characters.
    2740            8 : // For a NumericLiteral, the stored value is the toString() representation of the number. For example 1, 1.00, and 1e0 are all stored as just "1".

    2754            8 : // or any literal of a template, this means quotes have been removed and escapes have been converted to actual characters.

    2786            8 : // dprint-ignore
    2787            8 : export const enum TokenFlags {
    2788            8 :     None = 0,
    2789            8 :     /** @internal */
    2790            8 :     PrecedingLineBreak = 1 << 0,
    2791            8 :     /** @internal */
    2792            8 :     PrecedingJSDocComment = 1 << 1,
    2793            8 :     /** @internal */
    2794            8 :     Unterminated = 1 << 2,
    2795            8 :     /** @internal */
    2796            8 :     ExtendedUnicodeEscape = 1 << 3,     // e.g. `\u{10ffff}`
    2797            8 :     Scientific = 1 << 4,                // e.g. `10e2`
    2798            8 :     Octal = 1 << 5,                     // e.g. `0777`
    2799            8 :     HexSpecifier = 1 << 6,              // e.g. `0x00000000`
    2800            8 :     BinarySpecifier = 1 << 7,           // e.g. `0b0110010000000000`
    2801            8 :     OctalSpecifier = 1 << 8,            // e.g. `0o777`
    2802            8 :     /** @internal */
    2803            8 :     ContainsSeparator = 1 << 9,         // e.g. `0b1100_0101`
    2804            8 :     /** @internal */
    2805            8 :     UnicodeEscape = 1 << 10,            // e.g. `\u00a0`
    2806            8 :     /** @internal */
    2807            8 :     ContainsInvalidEscape = 1 << 11,    // e.g. `\uhello`
    2808            8 :     /** @internal */
    2809            8 :     HexEscape = 1 << 12,                // e.g. `\xa0`
    2810            8 :     /** @internal */
    2811            8 :     ContainsLeadingZero = 1 << 13,      // e.g. `0888`
    2812            8 :     /** @internal */
    2813            8 :     ContainsInvalidSeparator = 1 << 14, // e.g. `0_1`
    2814            8 :     /** @internal */
    2815            8 :     BinaryOrOctalSpecifier = BinarySpecifier | OctalSpecifier,
    2816            8 :     /** @internal */
    2817            8 :     WithSpecifier = HexSpecifier | BinaryOrOctalSpecifier,
    2818            8 :     /** @internal */
    2819            8 :     StringLiteralFlags = HexEscape | UnicodeEscape | ExtendedUnicodeEscape | ContainsInvalidEscape,
    2820            8 :     /** @internal */
    2821            8 :     NumericLiteralFlags = Scientific | Octal | ContainsLeadingZero | WithSpecifier | ContainsSeparator | ContainsInvalidSeparator,
    2822            8 :     /** @internal */
    2823            8 :     TemplateLiteralLikeFlags = HexEscape | UnicodeEscape | ExtendedUnicodeEscape | ContainsInvalidEscape,
    2824            8 :     /** @internal */
    2825            8 :     IsInvalid = Octal | ContainsLeadingZero | ContainsInvalidSeparator | ContainsInvalidEscape,
    2826            8 : }
    2827            8 :

    3647            8 : // In case of:
    3648            8 : // import "mod"  => importClause = undefined, moduleSpecifier = "mod"
    3649            8 : // In rest of the cases, module specifier is string literal corresponding to module
    3650            8 : // ImportClause information is shown at its declaration below.

    3669            8 : 
    3670            8 : // In case of:
    3671            8 : // import d from "mod" => name = d, namedBinding = undefined
    3672            8 : // import * as ns from "mod" => name = undefined, namedBinding: NamespaceImport = { name: ns }
    3673            8 : // import d, * as ns from "mod" => name = d, namedBinding: NamespaceImport = { name: ns }
    3674            8 : // import { a, b as x } from "mod" => name = undefined, namedBinding: NamedImports = { elements: [{ name: a }, { name: x, propertyName: b}]}
    3675            8 : // import d, { a, b as x } from "mod" => name = d, namedBinding: NamedImports = { elements: [{ name: a }, { name: x, propertyName: b}]}

    3681            8 :     readonly namedBindings?: NamedImportBindings;

    4100            8 : // NOTE: Ensure this is up-to-date with src/debug/debug.ts
    4101            8 : // dprint-ignore
    4102            8 : /** @internal */
    4103            8 : export const enum FlowFlags {
    4104            8 :     Unreachable    = 1 << 0,  // Unreachable code
    4105            8 :     Start          = 1 << 1,  // Start of flow graph
    4106            8 :     BranchLabel    = 1 << 2,  // Non-looping junction
    4107            8 :     LoopLabel      = 1 << 3,  // Looping junction
    4108            8 :     Assignment     = 1 << 4,  // Assignment
    4109            8 :     TrueCondition  = 1 << 5,  // Condition known to be true
    4110            8 :     FalseCondition = 1 << 6,  // Condition known to be false
    4111            8 :     SwitchClause   = 1 << 7,  // Switch statement clause
    4112            8 :     ArrayMutation  = 1 << 8,  // Potential array mutation
    4113            8 :     Call           = 1 << 9,  // Potential assertion call
    4114            8 :     ReduceLabel    = 1 << 10, // Temporarily reduce antecedents of label
    4115            8 :     Referenced     = 1 << 11, // Referenced as antecedent once
    4116            8 :     Shared         = 1 << 12, // Referenced as antecedent more than once
    4117            8 : 
    4118            8 :     Label = BranchLabel | LoopLabel,
    4119            8 :     Condition = TrueCondition | FalseCondition,
    4120            8 : }
    4121            8 : 
    4122            8 : /** @internal */
    4123            8 : export type FlowNode =
    4124            8 :     | FlowUnreachable
    4125            8 :     | FlowStart
    4126            8 :     | FlowLabel
    4127            8 :     | FlowAssignment
    4128            8 :     | FlowCondition
    4129            8 :     | FlowSwitchClause
    4130            8 :     | FlowArrayMutation
    4131            8 :     | FlowCall
    4132            8 :     | FlowReduceLabel;
    4133            8 : 
    4134            8 : /** @internal */
    4135            8 : export interface FlowNodeBase {
    4136            8 :     flags: FlowFlags;
    4137            8 :     id: number; // Node id used by flow type cache in checker
    4138            8 :     node: unknown; // Node or other data
    4139            8 :     antecedent: FlowNode | FlowNode[] | undefined;
    4140            8 : }
    4141            8 : 
    4142            8 : /** @internal */
    4143            8 : export interface FlowUnreachable extends FlowNodeBase {
    4144            8 :     node: undefined;
    4145            8 :     antecedent: undefined;
    4146            8 : }
    4147            8 : 
    4148            8 : // FlowStart represents the start of a control flow. For a function expression or arrow
    4149            8 : // function, the node property references the function (which in turn has a flowNode
    4150            8 : // property for the containing control flow).
    4151            8 : /** @internal */
    4152            8 : export interface FlowStart extends FlowNodeBase {
    4153            8 :     node: FunctionExpression | ArrowFunction | MethodDeclaration | GetAccessorDeclaration | SetAccessorDeclaration | undefined;
    4154            8 :     antecedent: undefined;
    4155            8 : }
    4156            8 : 
    4157            8 : // FlowLabel represents a junction with multiple possible preceding control flows.
    4158            8 : /** @internal */
    4159            8 : export interface FlowLabel extends FlowNodeBase {
    4160            8 :     node: undefined;
    4161            8 :     antecedent: FlowNode[] | undefined;
    4162            8 : }
    4163            8 : 
    4164            8 : // FlowAssignment represents a node that assigns a value to a narrowable reference,
    4165            8 : // i.e. an identifier or a dotted name that starts with an identifier or 'this'.
    4166            8 : /** @internal */
    4167            8 : export interface FlowAssignment extends FlowNodeBase {
    4168            8 :     node: Expression | VariableDeclaration | BindingElement;
    4169            8 :     antecedent: FlowNode;
    4170            8 : }
    4171            8 : 
    4172            8 : /** @internal */
    4173            8 : export interface FlowCall extends FlowNodeBase {
    4174            8 :     node: CallExpression;
    4175            8 :     antecedent: FlowNode;
    4176            8 : }
    4177            8 : 
    4178            8 : // FlowCondition represents a condition that is known to be true or false at the
    4179            8 : // node's location in the control flow.
    4180            8 : /** @internal */
    4181            8 : export interface FlowCondition extends FlowNodeBase {
    4182            8 :     node: Expression;
    4183            8 :     antecedent: FlowNode;
    4184            8 : }
    4185            8 : 
    4186            8 : // dprint-ignore
    4187            8 : /** @internal */
    4188            8 : export interface FlowSwitchClause extends FlowNodeBase {
    4189            8 :     node: FlowSwitchClauseData;
    4190            8 :     antecedent: FlowNode;
    4191            8 : }
    4192            8 : 
    4193            8 : /** @internal */
    4194            8 : export interface FlowSwitchClauseData {
    4195            8 :     switchStatement: SwitchStatement;
    4196            8 :     clauseStart: number; // Start index of case/default clause range
    4197            8 :     clauseEnd: number; // End index of case/default clause range
    4198            8 : }
    4199            8 : 
    4200            8 : // FlowArrayMutation represents a node potentially mutates an array, i.e. an
    4201            8 : // operation of the form 'x.push(value)', 'x.unshift(value)' or 'x[n] = value'.

    4748            8 :     /**
    4749            8 :      * Calculates the final resolution mode for a given module reference node. This function only returns a result when module resolution
    4750            8 :      * settings allow differing resolution between ESM imports and CJS requires, or when a mode is explicitly provided via import attributes,
    4751            8 :      * which cause an `import` or `require` condition to be used during resolution regardless of module resolution settings. In absence of
    4752            8 :      * overriding attributes, and in modes that support differing resolution, the result indicates the syntax the usage would emit to JavaScript.
    4753            8 :      * Some examples:
    4754            8 :      *
    4755            8 :      * ```ts
    4756            8 :      * // tsc foo.mts --module nodenext
    4757            8 :      * import {} from "mod";
    4758            8 :      * // Result: ESNext - the import emits as ESM due to `impliedNodeFormat` set by .mts file extension
    4759            8 :      *
    4760            8 :      * // tsc foo.cts --module nodenext
    4761            8 :      * import {} from "mod";
    4762            8 :      * // Result: CommonJS - the import emits as CJS due to `impliedNodeFormat` set by .cts file extension
    4763            8 :      *
    4764            8 :      * // tsc foo.ts --module preserve --moduleResolution bundler
    4765            8 :      * import {} from "mod";
    4766            8 :      * // Result: ESNext - the import emits as ESM due to `--module preserve` and `--moduleResolution bundler`
    4767            8 :      * // supports conditional imports/exports
    4768            8 :      *
    4769            8 :      * // tsc foo.ts --module preserve --moduleResolution node10
    4770            8 :      * import {} from "mod";
    4771            8 :      * // Result: undefined - the import emits as ESM due to `--module preserve`, but `--moduleResolution node10`
    4772            8 :      * // does not support conditional imports/exports
    4773            8 :      *
    4774            8 :      * // tsc foo.ts --module commonjs --moduleResolution node10
    4775            8 :      * import type {} from "mod" with { "resolution-mode": "import" };
    4776            8 :      * // Result: ESNext - conditional imports/exports always supported with "resolution-mode" attribute
    4777            8 :      * ```
    4778            8 :      */
    4779            8 :     getModeForUsageLocation(file: SourceFile, usage: StringLiteralLike): ResolutionMode;
    4780            8 :     /**
    4781            8 :      * Calculates the final resolution mode for an import at some index within a file's `imports` list. This function only returns a result

    4783            8 :      * via import attributes, which cause an `import` or `require` condition to be used during resolution regardless of module resolution
    4784            8 :      * settings. In absence of overriding attributes, and in modes that support differing resolution, the result indicates the syntax the
    4785            8 :      * usage would emit to JavaScript. Some examples:
    4786            8 :      *
    4787            8 :      * ```ts
    4788            8 :      * // tsc foo.mts --module nodenext

    4798            8 :      * // Result: ESNext - the import emits as ESM due to `--module preserve` and `--moduleResolution bundler`

    5405            8 : export const enum NodeBuilderFlags {
    5406            8 :     None                                    = 0,
    5407            8 :     // Options
    5408            8 :     NoTruncation                            = 1 << 0,   // Don't truncate result
    5409            8 :     WriteArrayAsGenericType                 = 1 << 1,   // Write Array<T> instead T[]
    5410            8 :     GenerateNamesForShadowedTypeParams      = 1 << 2,   // When a type parameter T is shadowing another T, generate a name for it so it can still be referenced
    5411            8 :     UseStructuralFallback                   = 1 << 3,   // When an alias cannot be named by its symbol, rather than report an error, fallback to a structural printout if possible
    5412            8 :     ForbidIndexedAccessSymbolReferences     = 1 << 4,   // Forbid references like `I["a"]["b"]` - print `typeof I.a<x>.b<y>` instead
    5413            8 :     WriteTypeArgumentsOfSignature           = 1 << 5,   // Write the type arguments instead of type parameters of the signature
    5414            8 :     UseFullyQualifiedType                   = 1 << 6,   // Write out the fully qualified type name (eg. Module.Type, instead of Type)
    5415            8 :     UseOnlyExternalAliasing                 = 1 << 7,   // Only use external aliases for a symbol
    5416            8 :     SuppressAnyReturnType                   = 1 << 8,   // If the return type is any-like and can be elided, don't offer a return type.
    5417            8 :     WriteTypeParametersInQualifiedName      = 1 << 9,
    5418            8 :     MultilineObjectLiterals                 = 1 << 10,  // Always write object literals across multiple lines
    5419            8 :     WriteClassExpressionAsTypeLiteral       = 1 << 11,  // Write class {} as { new(): {} } - used for mixin declaration emit
    5420            8 :     UseTypeOfFunction                       = 1 << 12,  // Build using typeof instead of function type literal
    5421            8 :     OmitParameterModifiers                  = 1 << 13,  // Omit modifiers on parameters
    5422            8 :     UseAliasDefinedOutsideCurrentScope      = 1 << 14,  // Allow non-visible aliases
    5423            8 :     UseSingleQuotesForStringLiteralType     = 1 << 28,  // Use single quotes for string literal type
    5424            8 :     NoTypeReduction                         = 1 << 29,  // Don't call getReducedType
    5425            8 :     OmitThisParameter                       = 1 << 25,
    5426            8 : 
    5427            8 :     // Error handling
    5428            8 :     AllowThisInObjectLiteral                = 1 << 15,
    5429            8 :     AllowQualifiedNameInPlaceOfIdentifier   = 1 << 16,
    5430            8 :     AllowAnonymousIdentifier                = 1 << 17,
    5431            8 :     AllowEmptyUnionOrIntersection           = 1 << 18,
    5432            8 :     AllowEmptyTuple                         = 1 << 19,
    5433            8 :     AllowUniqueESSymbolType                 = 1 << 20,
    5434            8 :     AllowEmptyIndexInfoType                 = 1 << 21,
    5435            8 :     /** @internal */ WriteComputedProps      = 1 << 30, // { [E.A]: 1 }
    5436            8 :     /** @internal */ NoSyntacticPrinter     = 1 << 31,
    5437            8 :     // Errors (cont.)
    5438            8 :     AllowNodeModulesRelativePaths           = 1 << 26,
    5439            8 :     /** @internal */ DoNotIncludeSymbolChain = 1 << 27,    // Skip looking up and printing an accessible symbol chain
    5440            8 :     /** @internal */ AllowUnresolvedNames = 1 << 32,
    5441            8 : 
    5442            8 :     IgnoreErrors = AllowThisInObjectLiteral | AllowQualifiedNameInPlaceOfIdentifier | AllowAnonymousIdentifier | AllowEmptyUnionOrIntersection | AllowEmptyTuple | AllowEmptyIndexInfoType | AllowNodeModulesRelativePaths,
    5443            8 : 
    5444            8 :     // State
    5445            8 :     InObjectTypeLiteral                     = 1 << 22,
    5446            8 :     InTypeAlias                             = 1 << 23,    // Writing type in type alias declaration
    5447            8 :     InInitialEntityName                     = 1 << 24,    // Set when writing the LHS of an entity name or entity name expression
    5448            8 : }

    5450            8 : // Ensure the shared flags between this and `NodeBuilderFlags` stay in alignment
    5451            8 : // dprint-ignore
    5452            8 : export const enum TypeFormatFlags {
    5453            8 :     None                                    = 0,
    5454            8 :     NoTruncation                            = 1 << 0,  // Don't truncate typeToString result
    5455            8 :     WriteArrayAsGenericType                 = 1 << 1,  // Write Array<T> instead T[]
    5456            8 :     GenerateNamesForShadowedTypeParams      = 1 << 2,   // When a type parameter T is shadowing another T, generate a name for it so it can still be referenced
    5457            8 :     UseStructuralFallback                   = 1 << 3,   // When an alias cannot be named by its symbol, rather than report an error, fallback to a structural printout if possible
    5458            8 :     // hole because there's a hole in node builder flags
    5459            8 :     WriteTypeArgumentsOfSignature           = 1 << 5,  // Write the type arguments instead of type parameters of the signature
    5460            8 :     UseFullyQualifiedType                   = 1 << 6,  // Write out the fully qualified type name (eg. Module.Type, instead of Type)
    5461            8 :     // hole because `UseOnlyExternalAliasing` is here in node builder flags, but functions which take old flags use `SymbolFormatFlags` instead
    5462            8 :     SuppressAnyReturnType                   = 1 << 8,  // If the return type is any-like, don't offer a return type.
    5463            8 :     // hole because `WriteTypeParametersInQualifiedName` is here in node builder flags, but functions which take old flags use `SymbolFormatFlags` for this instead
    5464            8 :     MultilineObjectLiterals                 = 1 << 10, // Always print object literals across multiple lines (only used to map into node builder flags)
    5465            8 :     WriteClassExpressionAsTypeLiteral       = 1 << 11, // Write a type literal instead of (Anonymous class)
    5466            8 :     UseTypeOfFunction                       = 1 << 12, // Write typeof instead of function type literal
    5467            8 :     OmitParameterModifiers                  = 1 << 13, // Omit modifiers on parameters
    5468            8 : 
    5469            8 :     UseAliasDefinedOutsideCurrentScope      = 1 << 14, // For a `type T = ... ` defined in a different file, write `T` instead of its value, even though `T` can't be accessed in the current scope.
    5470            8 :     UseSingleQuotesForStringLiteralType     = 1 << 28, // Use single quotes for string literal type
    5471            8 :     NoTypeReduction                         = 1 << 29, // Don't call getReducedType
    5472            8 :     OmitThisParameter                       = 1 << 25,
    5473            8 : 
    5474            8 :     // Error Handling
    5475            8 :     AllowUniqueESSymbolType                 = 1 << 20, // This is bit 20 to align with the same bit in `NodeBuilderFlags`
    5476            8 : 
    5477            8 :     // TypeFormatFlags exclusive
    5478            8 :     AddUndefined                            = 1 << 17, // Add undefined to types of initialized, non-optional parameters
    5479            8 :     WriteArrowStyleSignature                = 1 << 18, // Write arrow style signature
    5480            8 : 
    5481            8 :     // State
    5482            8 :     InArrayType                             = 1 << 19, // Writing an array element type
    5483            8 :     InElementType                           = 1 << 21, // Writing an array or union element type
    5484            8 :     InFirstTypeArgument                     = 1 << 22, // Writing first type argument of the instantiated type
    5485            8 :     InTypeAlias                             = 1 << 23, // Writing type in type alias declaration
    5486            8 : 
    5487            8 :     NodeBuilderFlagsMask = NoTruncation | WriteArrayAsGenericType | GenerateNamesForShadowedTypeParams | UseStructuralFallback | WriteTypeArgumentsOfSignature |
    5488            8 :         UseFullyQualifiedType | SuppressAnyReturnType | MultilineObjectLiterals | WriteClassExpressionAsTypeLiteral |
    5489            8 :         UseTypeOfFunction | OmitParameterModifiers | UseAliasDefinedOutsideCurrentScope | AllowUniqueESSymbolType | InTypeAlias |
    5490            8 :         UseSingleQuotesForStringLiteralType | NoTypeReduction | OmitThisParameter,
    5491            8 : }
    5492            8 : 
    5493            8 : // dprint-ignore
    5494            8 : export const enum SymbolFormatFlags {
    5495            8 :     None                                    = 0,
    5496            8 : 
    5497            8 :     // Write symbols's type argument if it is instantiated symbol
    5498            8 :     // eg. class C<T> { p: T }   <-- Show p as C<T>.p here
    5499            8 :     //     var a: C<number>;
    5500            8 :     //     var p = a.p; <--- Here p is property of C<number> so show it as C<number>.p instead of just C.p
    5501            8 :     WriteTypeParametersOrArguments          = 1 << 0,
    5502            8 : 
    5503            8 :     // Use only external alias information to get the symbol name in the given context
    5504            8 :     // eg.  module m { export class c { } } import x = m.c;
    5505            8 :     // When this flag is specified m.c will be used to refer to the class instead of alias symbol x
    5506            8 :     UseOnlyExternalAliasing                 = 1 << 1,
    5507            8 : 
    5508            8 :     // Build symbol name using any nodes needed, instead of just components of an entity name
    5509            8 :     AllowAnyNodeKind                        = 1 << 2,
    5510            8 : 
    5511            8 :     // Prefer aliases which are not directly visible
    5512            8 :     UseAliasDefinedOutsideCurrentScope      = 1 << 3,
    5513            8 : 
    5514            8 :     // { [E.A]: 1 }
    5515            8 :     /** @internal */ WriteComputedProps      = 1 << 4,
    5516            8 : 
    5517            8 :     // Skip building an accessible symbol chain
    5518            8 :     /** @internal */ DoNotIncludeSymbolChain = 1 << 5,
    5519            8 : }

    5817            8 : export const enum SymbolFlags {
    5818            8 :     None                    = 0,
    5819            8 :     FunctionScopedVariable  = 1 << 0,   // Variable (var) or parameter
    5820            8 :     BlockScopedVariable     = 1 << 1,   // A block-scoped variable (let or const)
    5821            8 :     Property                = 1 << 2,   // Property or enum member
    5822            8 :     EnumMember              = 1 << 3,   // Enum member
    5823            8 :     Function                = 1 << 4,   // Function
    5824            8 :     Class                   = 1 << 5,   // Class
    5825            8 :     Interface               = 1 << 6,   // Interface
    5826            8 :     ConstEnum               = 1 << 7,   // Const enum
    5827            8 :     RegularEnum             = 1 << 8,   // Enum
    5828            8 :     ValueModule             = 1 << 9,   // Instantiated module
    5829            8 :     NamespaceModule         = 1 << 10,  // Uninstantiated module
    5830            8 :     TypeLiteral             = 1 << 11,  // Type Literal or mapped type
    5831            8 :     ObjectLiteral           = 1 << 12,  // Object Literal
    5832            8 :     Method                  = 1 << 13,  // Method
    5833            8 :     Constructor             = 1 << 14,  // Constructor
    5834            8 :     GetAccessor             = 1 << 15,  // Get accessor
    5835            8 :     SetAccessor             = 1 << 16,  // Set accessor
    5836            8 :     Signature               = 1 << 17,  // Call, construct, or index signature
    5837            8 :     TypeParameter           = 1 << 18,  // Type parameter
    5838            8 :     TypeAlias               = 1 << 19,  // Type alias
    5839            8 :     ExportValue             = 1 << 20,  // Exported value marker (see comment in declareModuleMember in binder)
    5840            8 :     Alias                   = 1 << 21,  // An alias for another symbol (see comment in isAliasSymbolDeclaration in checker)
    5841            8 :     Prototype               = 1 << 22,  // Prototype property (no source representation)
    5842            8 :     ExportStar              = 1 << 23,  // Export * declaration
    5843            8 :     Optional                = 1 << 24,  // Optional property
    5844            8 :     Transient               = 1 << 25,  // Transient symbol (created during type check)
    5845            8 :     Assignment              = 1 << 26,  // Assignment treated as declaration (eg `this.prop = 1`)
    5846            8 :     ModuleExports           = 1 << 27,  // Symbol for CommonJS `module` of `module.exports`
    5847            8 :     All = -1,
    5848            8 : 
    5849            8 :     Enum = RegularEnum | ConstEnum,
    5850            8 :     Variable = FunctionScopedVariable | BlockScopedVariable,
    5851            8 :     Value = Variable | Property | EnumMember | ObjectLiteral | Function | Class | Enum | ValueModule | Method | GetAccessor | SetAccessor,
    5852            8 :     Type = Class | Interface | Enum | EnumMember | TypeLiteral | TypeParameter | TypeAlias,
    5853            8 :     Namespace = ValueModule | NamespaceModule | Enum,
    5854            8 :     Module = ValueModule | NamespaceModule,
    5855            8 :     Accessor = GetAccessor | SetAccessor,
    5856            8 : 
    5857            8 :     // Variables can be redeclared, but can not redeclare a block-scoped declaration with the
    5858            8 :     // same name, or any other value that is not a variable, e.g. ValueModule or Class
    5859            8 :     FunctionScopedVariableExcludes = Value & ~FunctionScopedVariable,
    5860            8 : 
    5861            8 :     // Block-scoped declarations are not allowed to be re-declared
    5862            8 :     // they can not merge with anything in the value space
    5863            8 :     BlockScopedVariableExcludes = Value,
    5864            8 : 
    5865            8 :     ParameterExcludes = Value,
    5866            8 :     PropertyExcludes = None,
    5867            8 :     EnumMemberExcludes = Value | Type,
    5868            8 :     FunctionExcludes = Value & ~(Function | ValueModule | Class),
    5869            8 :     ClassExcludes = (Value | Type) & ~(ValueModule | Interface | Function), // class-interface mergability done in checker.ts
    5870            8 :     InterfaceExcludes = Type & ~(Interface | Class),
    5871            8 :     RegularEnumExcludes = (Value | Type) & ~(RegularEnum | ValueModule), // regular enums merge only with regular enums and modules
    5872            8 :     ConstEnumExcludes = (Value | Type) & ~ConstEnum, // const enums merge only with const enums
    5873            8 :     ValueModuleExcludes = Value & ~(Function | Class | RegularEnum | ValueModule),
    5874            8 :     NamespaceModuleExcludes = 0,
    5875            8 :     MethodExcludes = Value & ~Method,
    5876            8 :     GetAccessorExcludes = Value & ~SetAccessor,
    5877            8 :     SetAccessorExcludes = Value & ~GetAccessor,
    5878            8 :     AccessorExcludes = Value & ~Accessor,
    5879            8 :     TypeParameterExcludes = Type & ~TypeParameter,
    5880            8 :     TypeAliasExcludes = Type,
    5881            8 :     AliasExcludes = Alias,
    5882            8 : 
    5883            8 :     ModuleMember = Variable | Function | Class | Interface | Enum | Module | TypeAlias | Alias,
    5884            8 : 
    5885            8 :     ExportHasLocal = Function | Class | Enum | ValueModule,
    5886            8 : 
    5887            8 :     BlockScoped = BlockScopedVariable | Class | Enum,
    5888            8 : 
    5889            8 :     PropertyOrAccessor = Property | Accessor,
    5890            8 : 
    5891            8 :     ClassMember = Method | Accessor | Property,
    5892            8 : 
    5893            8 :     /** @internal */
    5894            8 :     ExportSupportsDefaultModifier = Class | Function | Interface,
    5895            8 : 
    5896            8 :     /** @internal */
    5897            8 :     ExportDoesNotSupportDefaultModifier = ~ExportSupportsDefaultModifier,
    5898            8 : 
    5899            8 :     /** @internal */
    5900            8 :     // The set of things we consider semantically classifiable.  Used to speed up the LS during
    5901            8 :     // classification.
    5902            8 :     Classifiable = Class | Enum | TypeAlias | Interface | TypeParameter | Module | Alias,

    6063            8 : 
    6064            8 : /**
    6065            8 :  * This represents a string whose leading underscore have been escaped by adding extra leading underscores.
    6066            8 :  * The shape of this brand is rather unique compared to others we've used.
    6067            8 :  * Instead of just an intersection of a string and an object, it is that union-ed
    6068            8 :  * with an intersection of void and an object. This makes it wholly incompatible
    6069            8 :  * with a normal string (which is good, it cannot be misused on assignment or on usage),
    6070            8 :  * while still being comparable with a normal string via === (also good) and castable from a string.
    6071            8 :  */
    6072            8 : export type __String = (string & { __escapedIdentifier: void; }) | (void & { __escapedIdentifier: void; }) | InternalSymbolName;
    6073            8 : 
    6074            8 : /** @deprecated Use ReadonlyMap<__String, T> instead. */
    6075            8 : export type ReadonlyUnderscoreEscapedMap<T> = ReadonlyMap<__String, T>;
    6076            8 : 
    6077            8 : /** @deprecated Use Map<__String, T> instead. */
    6078            8 : export type UnderscoreEscapedMap<T> = Map<__String, T>;
    6079            8 :

    6284            8 :     /** @internal */

    6286            8 :     /** @internal */

    6292            8 : }

    6370            8 : // Types included in TypeFlags.ObjectFlagsType have an objectFlags property. Some ObjectFlags
    6371            8 : // are specific to certain types and reuse the same bit position. Those ObjectFlags require a check
    6372            8 : // for a certain TypeFlags value to determine their meaning.
    6373            8 : // dprint-ignore
    6374            8 : export const enum ObjectFlags {
    6375            8 :     None             = 0,
    6376            8 :     Class            = 1 << 0,  // Class
    6377            8 :     Interface        = 1 << 1,  // Interface
    6378            8 :     Reference        = 1 << 2,  // Generic type reference
    6379            8 :     Tuple            = 1 << 3,  // Synthesized generic tuple type
    6380            8 :     Anonymous        = 1 << 4,  // Anonymous
    6381            8 :     Mapped           = 1 << 5,  // Mapped
    6382            8 :     Instantiated     = 1 << 6,  // Instantiated anonymous or mapped type
    6383            8 :     ObjectLiteral    = 1 << 7,  // Originates in an object literal
    6384            8 :     EvolvingArray    = 1 << 8,  // Evolving array type
    6385            8 :     ObjectLiteralPatternWithComputedProperties = 1 << 9,  // Object literal pattern with computed properties
    6386            8 :     ReverseMapped    = 1 << 10, // Object contains a property from a reverse-mapped type
    6387            8 :     JsxAttributes    = 1 << 11, // Jsx attributes type
    6388            8 :     JSLiteral        = 1 << 12, // Object type declared in JS - disables errors on read/write of nonexisting members
    6389            8 :     FreshLiteral     = 1 << 13, // Fresh object literal
    6390            8 :     ArrayLiteral     = 1 << 14, // Originates in an array literal
    6391            8 :     /** @internal */
    6392            8 :     PrimitiveUnion   = 1 << 15, // Union of only primitive types
    6393            8 :     /** @internal */
    6394            8 :     ContainsWideningType = 1 << 16, // Type is or contains undefined or null widening type
    6395            8 :     /** @internal */
    6396            8 :     ContainsObjectOrArrayLiteral = 1 << 17, // Type is or contains object literal type
    6397            8 :     /** @internal */
    6398            8 :     NonInferrableType = 1 << 18, // Type is or contains anyFunctionType or silentNeverType
    6399            8 :     /** @internal */
    6400            8 :     CouldContainTypeVariablesComputed = 1 << 19, // CouldContainTypeVariables flag has been computed
    6401            8 :     /** @internal */
    6402            8 :     CouldContainTypeVariables = 1 << 20, // Type could contain a type variable
    6403            8 : 
    6404            8 :     ClassOrInterface = Class | Interface,
    6405            8 :     /** @internal */
    6406            8 :     RequiresWidening = ContainsWideningType | ContainsObjectOrArrayLiteral,
    6407            8 :     /** @internal */
    6408            8 :     PropagatingFlags = ContainsWideningType | ContainsObjectOrArrayLiteral | NonInferrableType,
    6409            8 :     /** @internal */
    6410            8 :     InstantiatedMapped = Mapped | Instantiated,
    6411            8 :     // Object flags that uniquely identify the kind of ObjectType
    6412            8 :     /** @internal */
    6413            8 :     ObjectTypeKindMask = ClassOrInterface | Reference | Tuple | Anonymous | Mapped | ReverseMapped | EvolvingArray,
    6414            8 : 
    6415            8 :     // Flags that require TypeFlags.Object
    6416            8 :     ContainsSpread   = 1 << 21,  // Object literal contains spread operation
    6417            8 :     ObjectRestType   = 1 << 22,  // Originates in object rest declaration
    6418            8 :     InstantiationExpressionType = 1 << 23,  // Originates in instantiation expression
    6419            8 :     SingleSignatureType = 1 << 27,  // A single signature type extracted from a potentially broader type
    6420            8 :     /** @internal */
    6421            8 :     IsClassInstanceClone = 1 << 24, // Type is a clone of a class instance type
    6422            8 :     // Flags that require TypeFlags.Object and ObjectFlags.Reference
    6423            8 :     /** @internal */
    6424            8 :     IdenticalBaseTypeCalculated = 1 << 25, // has had `getSingleBaseForNonAugmentingSubtype` invoked on it already
    6425            8 :     /** @internal */
    6426            8 :     IdenticalBaseTypeExists = 1 << 26, // has a defined cachedEquivalentBaseType member
    6427            8 : 
    6428            8 :     // Flags that require TypeFlags.UnionOrIntersection or TypeFlags.Substitution
    6429            8 :     /** @internal */
    6430            8 :     IsGenericTypeComputed = 1 << 21, // IsGenericObjectType flag has been computed
    6431            8 :     /** @internal */
    6432            8 :     IsGenericObjectType = 1 << 22, // Union or intersection contains generic object type
    6433            8 :     /** @internal */
    6434            8 :     IsGenericIndexType = 1 << 23, // Union or intersection contains generic index type
    6435            8 :     /** @internal */
    6436            8 :     IsGenericType = IsGenericObjectType | IsGenericIndexType,
    6437            8 : 
    6438            8 :     // Flags that require TypeFlags.Union
    6439            8 :     /** @internal */
    6440            8 :     ContainsIntersections = 1 << 24, // Union contains intersections
    6441            8 :     /** @internal */
    6442            8 :     IsUnknownLikeUnionComputed = 1 << 25, // IsUnknownLikeUnion flag has been computed
    6443            8 :     /** @internal */
    6444            8 :     IsUnknownLikeUnion = 1 << 26, // Union of null, undefined, and empty object type
    6445            8 :     /** @internal */
    6446            8 : 
    6447            8 :     // Flags that require TypeFlags.Intersection
    6448            8 :     /** @internal */
    6449            8 :     IsNeverIntersectionComputed = 1 << 24, // IsNeverLike flag has been computed
    6450            8 :     /** @internal */
    6451            8 :     IsNeverIntersection = 1 << 25, // Intersection reduces to never
    6452            8 :     /** @internal */
    6453            8 :     IsConstrainedTypeVariable = 1 << 26, // T & C, where T's constraint and C are primitives, object, or {}
    6454            8 : }
    6455            8 : 
    6456            8 : /** @internal */
    6457            8 : export type ObjectFlagsType = NullableType | ObjectType | UnionType | IntersectionType;

    6497            8 : /**
    6498            8 :  * Type references (ObjectFlags.Reference). When a class or interface has type parameters or
    6499            8 :  * a "this" type, references to the class or interface are made using type references. The
    6500            8 :  * typeArguments property specifies the types to substitute for the type parameters of the
    6501            8 :  * class or interface and optionally includes an extra element that specifies the type to
    6502            8 :  * substitute for "this" in the resulting instantiation. When no extra argument is present,
    6503            8 :  * the type reference itself is substituted for "this". The typeArguments property is undefined
    6504            8 :  * if the class or interface has no type parameters and the reference isn't specifying an
    6505            8 :  * explicit "this" argument.
    6506            8 :  */

    6532            8 :     Invariant     =      0,  // Neither covariant nor contravariant
    6533            8 :     Covariant     = 1 << 0,  // Covariant
    6534            8 :     Contravariant = 1 << 1,  // Contravariant
    6535            8 :     Bivariant     = Covariant | Contravariant,  // Both covariant and contravariant
    6536            8 :     Independent   = 1 << 2,  // Unwitnessed type parameter
    6537            8 :     VarianceMask  = Invariant | Covariant | Contravariant | Independent, // Mask containing all measured variances without the unmeasurable flag
    6538            8 :     Unmeasurable  = 1 << 3,  // Variance result is unusable - relationship relies on structural comparisons which are not reflected in generic relationships
    6539            8 :     Unreliable    = 1 << 4,  // Variance result is unreliable - checking may produce false negatives, but not false positives
    6540            8 :     AllowsStructuralFallback = Unmeasurable | Unreliable,
    6541            8 : }

    6831            8 : // Type parameter substitution (TypeFlags.Substitution)
    6832            8 : // Substitution types are created for type parameters or indexed access types that occur in the
    6833            8 : // true branch of a conditional type. For example, in 'T extends string ? Foo<T> : Bar<T>', the
    6834            8 : // reference to T in Foo<T> is resolved as a substitution type that substitutes 'string & T' for T.
    6835            8 : // Thus, if Foo has a 'string' constraint on its type parameter, T will satisfy it.
    6836            8 : // Substitution type are also created for NoInfer<T> types. Those are represented as substitution
    6837            8 : // types where the constraint is type 'unknown' (which is never generated for the case above).
    6838            8 : export interface SubstitutionType extends InstantiableType {
    6839            8 :     objectFlags: ObjectFlags;
    6840            8 :     baseType: Type; // Target type
    6841            8 :     constraint: Type; // Constraint that target type is known to satisfy
    6842            8 : }
    6843            8 :

    6849            8 : }

    6851            8 : export const enum SignatureKind {

    6856            8 : // dprint-ignore
    6857            8 : /** @internal */
    6858            8 : export const enum SignatureFlags {
    6859            8 :     None = 0,
    6860            8 : 
    6861            8 :     // Propagating flags
    6862            8 :     HasRestParameter = 1 << 0,          // Indicates last parameter is rest parameter
    6863            8 :     HasLiteralTypes = 1 << 1,           // Indicates signature is specialized
    6864            8 :     Abstract = 1 << 2,                  // Indicates signature comes from an abstract class, abstract construct signature, or abstract constructor type
    6865            8 : 
    6866            8 :     // Non-propagating flags
    6867            8 :     IsInnerCallChain = 1 << 3,          // Indicates signature comes from a CallChain nested in an outer OptionalChain
    6868            8 :     IsOuterCallChain = 1 << 4,          // Indicates signature comes from a CallChain that is the outermost chain of an optional expression
    6869            8 :     IsUntypedSignatureInJSFile = 1 << 5, // Indicates signature is from a js file and has no types
    6870            8 :     IsNonInferrable = 1 << 6,           // Indicates signature comes from a non-inferrable type
    6871            8 :     IsSignatureCandidateForOverloadFailure = 1 << 7,
    6872            8 : 
    6873            8 :     // We do not propagate `IsInnerCallChain` or `IsOuterCallChain` to instantiated signatures, as that would result in us
    6874            8 :     // attempting to add `| undefined` on each recursive call to `getReturnTypeOfSignature` when
    6875            8 :     // instantiating the return type.
    6876            8 :     PropagatingFlags = HasRestParameter | HasLiteralTypes | Abstract | IsUntypedSignatureInJSFile | IsSignatureCandidateForOverloadFailure,
    6877            8 : 
    6878            8 :     CallChainFlags = IsInnerCallChain | IsOuterCallChain,
    6879            8 : }
    6880            8 : 
    6881            8 : // dprint-ignore
    6882            8 : export interface Signature {
    6883            8 :     /** @internal */ flags: SignatureFlags;

    6885            8 :     declaration?: SignatureDeclaration | JSDocSignature; // Originating declaration

    6887            8 :     parameters: readonly Symbol[];               // Parameters
    6888            8 :     thisParameter?: Symbol;             // symbol of this-type parameter
    6889            8 :     /** @internal */
    6890            8 :     // See comment in `instantiateSignature` for why these are set lazily.
    6891            8 :     resolvedReturnType?: Type;          // Lazily set by `getReturnTypeOfSignature`.
    6892            8 :     /** @internal */
    6893            8 :     // Lazily set by `getTypePredicateOfSignature`.
    6894            8 :     // `undefined` indicates a type predicate that has not yet been computed.
    6895            8 :     // Uses a special `noTypePredicate` sentinel value to indicate that there is no type predicate. This looks like a TypePredicate at runtime to avoid polymorphism.
    6896            8 :     resolvedTypePredicate?: TypePredicate;
    6897            8 :     /** @internal */
    6898            8 :     minArgumentCount: number;           // Number of non-optional parameters
    6899            8 :     /** @internal */
    6900            8 :     resolvedMinArgumentCount?: number;  // Number of non-optional parameters (excluding trailing `void`)

    6903            8 :     /** @internal */
    6904            8 :     mapper?: TypeMapper;                // Instantiation mapper
    6905            8 :     /** @internal */

    6907            8 :     /** @internal */
    6908            8 :     compositeKind?: TypeFlags;          // TypeFlags.Union if the underlying signatures are from union members, otherwise TypeFlags.Intersection
    6909            8 :     /** @internal */
    6910            8 :     erasedSignatureCache?: Signature;   // Erased version of signature (deferred)
    6911            8 :     /** @internal */

    6917            8 :     /** @internal */
    6918            8 :     isolatedSignatureType?: ObjectType; // A manufactured type that just contains the signature for purposes of signature comparison
    6919            8 :     /** @internal */
    6920            8 :     instantiations?: Map<string, Signature>;    // Generic signature instantiation cache
    6921            8 :     /** @internal */
    6922            8 :     implementationSignatureCache?: Signature;  // Copy of the signature with fresh type parameters to use in checking the body of a potentially self-referential generic function (deferred)
    6923            8 : }

    6961            8 :     HomomorphicMappedType        = 1 << 3,  // Reverse inference for homomorphic mapped type
    6962            8 :     PartialHomomorphicMappedType = 1 << 4,  // Partial reverse inference for homomorphic mapped type
    6963            8 :     MappedTypeConstraint         = 1 << 5,  // Reverse inference for mapped type
    6964            8 :     ContravariantConditional     = 1 << 6,  // Conditional type in contravariant position
    6965            8 :     ReturnType                   = 1 << 7,  // Inference made from return type of generic function
    6966            8 :     LiteralKeyof                 = 1 << 8,  // Inference made from a string literal to a keyof T
    6967            8 :     NoConstraints                = 1 << 9,  // Don't infer from constraints of instantiable types
    6968            8 :     AlwaysStrict                 = 1 << 10, // Always use strict rules for contravariant inferences
    6969            8 :     MaxValue                     = 1 << 11, // Seed for inference priority tracking
    6970            8 : 
    6971            8 :     PriorityImpliesCombination = ReturnType | MappedTypeConstraint | LiteralKeyof, // These priorities imply that the resulting type should be a combination of all candidates
    6972            8 :     Circularity = -1,  // Inference circularity (value less than all other priorities)

    6996            8 : 
    6997            8 : /**
    6998            8 :  * Ternary values are defined such that
    6999            8 :  * x & y picks the lesser in the order False < Unknown < Maybe < True, and
    7000            8 :  * x | y picks the greater in the order False < Unknown < Maybe < True.
    7001            8 :  * Generally, Ternary.Maybe is used as the result of a relation that depends on itself, and
    7002            8 :  * Ternary.Unknown is used as the result of a variance check that depends on itself. We make
    7003            8 :  * a distinction because we don't want to cache circular variance check results.
    7004            8 :  *
    7005            8 :  * @internal
    7006            8 :  */
    7007            8 : export const enum Ternary {
    7008            8 :     False = 0,
    7009            8 :     Unknown = 1,
    7010            8 :     Maybe = 3,
    7011            8 :     True = -1,
    7012            8 : }
    7013            8 : 
    7014            8 : /** @internal */
    7015            8 : export type TypeComparer = (s: Type, t: Type, reportErrors?: boolean) => Ternary;

    7183            8 : export enum ModuleResolutionKind {
    7184            8 :     Classic = 1,
    7185            8 :     /**
    7186            8 :      * @deprecated
    7187            8 :      * `NodeJs` was renamed to `Node10` to better reflect the version of Node that it targets.
    7188            8 :      * Use the new name or consider switching to a modern module resolution target.
    7189            8 :      */
    7190            8 :     NodeJs = 2,
    7191            8 :     Node10 = 2,
    7192            8 :     // Starting with node12, node's module resolver has significant departures from traditional cjs resolution
    7193            8 :     // to better support ECMAScript modules and their use within node - however more features are still being added.
    7194            8 :     // TypeScript's Node ESM support was introduced after Node 12 went end-of-life, and Node 14 is the earliest stable
    7195            8 :     // version that supports both pattern trailers - *but*, Node 16 is the first version that also supports ECMAScript 2022.
    7196            8 :     // In turn, we offer both a `NodeNext` moving resolution target, and a `Node16` version-anchored resolution target
    7197            8 :     Node16 = 3,
    7198            8 :     NodeNext = 99, // Not simply `Node16` so that compiled code linked against TS can use the `Next` value reliably (same as with `ModuleKind`)
    7199            8 :     Bundler = 100,
    7200            8 : }

    7588            8 :     name: string;
    7589            8 :     type: "string" | "number" | "boolean" | "object" | "list" | "listOrElement" | Map<string, number | string>;    // a value of a primitive type, or an object literal mapping named values to actual values
    7590            8 :     isFilePath?: boolean;                                   // True if option value is a path or fileName
    7591            8 :     shortName?: string;                                     // A short mnemonic for convenience - for instance, 'h' can be used in place of 'help'
    7592            8 :     description?: DiagnosticMessage;                        // The message describing what the command line switch does.
    7593            8 :     defaultValueDescription?: string | number | boolean | DiagnosticMessage | undefined;   // The message describing what the dafault value is. string type is prepared for fixed chosen like "false" which do not need I18n.
    7594            8 :     paramType?: DiagnosticMessage;                          // The name to be used for a non-boolean option's parameter
    7595            8 :     isTSConfigOnly?: boolean;                               // True if option can only be specified via tsconfig.json file
    7596            8 :     isCommandLineOnly?: boolean;
    7597            8 :     showInSimplifiedHelpView?: boolean;
    7598            8 :     category?: DiagnosticMessage;
    7599            8 :     strictFlag?: true;                                      // true if the option is one of the flag under strict
    7600            8 :     allowJsFlag?: true;
    7601            8 :     affectsSourceFile?: true;                               // true if we should recreate SourceFiles after this option changes
    7602            8 :     affectsModuleResolution?: true;                         // currently same effect as `affectsSourceFile`
    7603            8 :     affectsBindDiagnostics?: true;                          // true if this affects binding (currently same effect as `affectsSourceFile`)
    7604            8 :     affectsSemanticDiagnostics?: true;                      // true if option affects semantic diagnostics
    7605            8 :     affectsEmit?: true;                                     // true if the options affects emit
    7606            8 :     affectsProgramStructure?: true;                         // true if program should be reconstructed from root files if option changes and does not affect module resolution as affectsModuleResolution indirectly means program needs to reconstructed
    7607            8 :     affectsDeclarationPath?: true;                          // true if the options affects declaration file path computed
    7608            8 :     affectsBuildInfo?: true;                                // true if this options should be emitted in buildInfo
    7609            8 :     transpileOptionValue?: boolean | undefined;             // If set this means that the option should be set to this value when transpiling
    7610            8 :     extraValidation?: (value: CompilerOptionsValue) => [DiagnosticMessage, ...string[]] | undefined; // Additional validation to be performed for the value to be valid
    7611            8 :     disallowNullOrUndefined?: true;                         // If set option does not allow setting null
    7612            8 :     allowConfigDirTemplateSubstitution?: true;              // If set option allows substitution of `${configDir}` in the value
    7613            8 : }

    8054            8 : export const enum TransformFlags {
    8055            8 :     None = 0,
    8056            8 : 
    8057            8 :     // Facts
    8058            8 :     // - Flags used to indicate that a node or subtree contains syntax that requires transformation.
    8059            8 :     ContainsTypeScript = 1 << 0,
    8060            8 :     ContainsJsx = 1 << 1,
    8061            8 :     ContainsESNext = 1 << 2,
    8062            8 :     ContainsES2022 = 1 << 3,
    8063            8 :     ContainsES2021 = 1 << 4,
    8064            8 :     ContainsES2020 = 1 << 5,
    8065            8 :     ContainsES2019 = 1 << 6,
    8066            8 :     ContainsES2018 = 1 << 7,
    8067            8 :     ContainsES2017 = 1 << 8,
    8068            8 :     ContainsES2016 = 1 << 9,
    8069            8 :     ContainsES2015 = 1 << 10,
    8070            8 :     ContainsGenerator = 1 << 11,
    8071            8 :     ContainsDestructuringAssignment = 1 << 12,
    8072            8 : 
    8073            8 :     // Markers
    8074            8 :     // - Flags used to indicate that a subtree contains a specific transformation.
    8075            8 :     ContainsTypeScriptClassSyntax = 1 << 13, // Property Initializers, Parameter Property Initializers
    8076            8 :     ContainsLexicalThis = 1 << 14,
    8077            8 :     ContainsRestOrSpread = 1 << 15,
    8078            8 :     ContainsObjectRestOrSpread = 1 << 16,
    8079            8 :     ContainsComputedPropertyName = 1 << 17,
    8080            8 :     ContainsBlockScopedBinding = 1 << 18,
    8081            8 :     ContainsBindingPattern = 1 << 19,
    8082            8 :     ContainsYield = 1 << 20,
    8083            8 :     ContainsAwait = 1 << 21,
    8084            8 :     ContainsHoistedDeclarationOrCompletion = 1 << 22,
    8085            8 :     ContainsDynamicImport = 1 << 23,
    8086            8 :     ContainsClassFields = 1 << 24,
    8087            8 :     ContainsDecorators = 1 << 25,
    8088            8 :     ContainsPossibleTopLevelAwait = 1 << 26,
    8089            8 :     ContainsLexicalSuper = 1 << 27,
    8090            8 :     ContainsUpdateExpressionForIdentifier = 1 << 28,
    8091            8 :     ContainsPrivateIdentifierInExpression = 1 << 29,
    8092            8 : 
    8093            8 :     HasComputedFlags = 1 << 31, // Transform flags have been computed.
    8094            8 : 
    8095            8 :     // Assertions
    8096            8 :     // - Bitmasks that are used to assert facts about the syntax of a node and its subtree.
    8097            8 :     AssertTypeScript = ContainsTypeScript,
    8098            8 :     AssertJsx = ContainsJsx,
    8099            8 :     AssertESNext = ContainsESNext,
    8100            8 :     AssertES2022 = ContainsES2022,
    8101            8 :     AssertES2021 = ContainsES2021,
    8102            8 :     AssertES2020 = ContainsES2020,
    8103            8 :     AssertES2019 = ContainsES2019,
    8104            8 :     AssertES2018 = ContainsES2018,
    8105            8 :     AssertES2017 = ContainsES2017,
    8106            8 :     AssertES2016 = ContainsES2016,
    8107            8 :     AssertES2015 = ContainsES2015,
    8108            8 :     AssertGenerator = ContainsGenerator,
    8109            8 :     AssertDestructuringAssignment = ContainsDestructuringAssignment,
    8110            8 : 
    8111            8 :     // Scope Exclusions
    8112            8 :     // - Bitmasks that exclude flags from propagating out of a specific context
    8113            8 :     //   into the subtree flags of their container.
    8114            8 :     OuterExpressionExcludes = HasComputedFlags,
    8115            8 :     PropertyAccessExcludes = OuterExpressionExcludes,
    8116            8 :     NodeExcludes = PropertyAccessExcludes,
    8117            8 :     ArrowFunctionExcludes = NodeExcludes | ContainsTypeScriptClassSyntax | ContainsBlockScopedBinding | ContainsYield | ContainsAwait | ContainsHoistedDeclarationOrCompletion | ContainsBindingPattern | ContainsObjectRestOrSpread | ContainsPossibleTopLevelAwait,
    8118            8 :     FunctionExcludes = NodeExcludes | ContainsTypeScriptClassSyntax | ContainsLexicalThis | ContainsLexicalSuper | ContainsBlockScopedBinding | ContainsYield | ContainsAwait | ContainsHoistedDeclarationOrCompletion | ContainsBindingPattern | ContainsObjectRestOrSpread | ContainsPossibleTopLevelAwait,
    8119            8 :     ConstructorExcludes = NodeExcludes | ContainsLexicalThis | ContainsLexicalSuper | ContainsBlockScopedBinding | ContainsYield | ContainsAwait | ContainsHoistedDeclarationOrCompletion | ContainsBindingPattern | ContainsObjectRestOrSpread | ContainsPossibleTopLevelAwait,
    8120            8 :     MethodOrAccessorExcludes = NodeExcludes | ContainsLexicalThis | ContainsLexicalSuper | ContainsBlockScopedBinding | ContainsYield | ContainsAwait | ContainsHoistedDeclarationOrCompletion | ContainsBindingPattern | ContainsObjectRestOrSpread,
    8121            8 :     PropertyExcludes = NodeExcludes | ContainsLexicalThis | ContainsLexicalSuper,
    8122            8 :     ClassExcludes = NodeExcludes | ContainsTypeScriptClassSyntax | ContainsComputedPropertyName,
    8123            8 :     ModuleExcludes = NodeExcludes | ContainsTypeScriptClassSyntax | ContainsLexicalThis | ContainsLexicalSuper | ContainsBlockScopedBinding | ContainsHoistedDeclarationOrCompletion | ContainsPossibleTopLevelAwait,
    8124            8 :     TypeExcludes = ~ContainsTypeScript,
    8125            8 :     ObjectLiteralExcludes = NodeExcludes | ContainsTypeScriptClassSyntax | ContainsComputedPropertyName | ContainsObjectRestOrSpread,
    8126            8 :     ArrayLiteralOrCallOrNewExcludes = NodeExcludes | ContainsRestOrSpread,
    8127            8 :     VariableDeclarationListExcludes = NodeExcludes | ContainsBindingPattern | ContainsObjectRestOrSpread,
    8128            8 :     ParameterExcludes = NodeExcludes,
    8129            8 :     CatchClauseExcludes = NodeExcludes | ContainsObjectRestOrSpread,
    8130            8 :     BindingPatternExcludes = NodeExcludes | ContainsRestOrSpread,
    8131            8 :     ContainsLexicalThisOrSuper = ContainsLexicalThis | ContainsLexicalSuper,
    8132            8 : 
    8133            8 :     // Propagating flags
    8134            8 :     // - Bitmasks for flags that should propagate from a child
    8135            8 :     PropertyNamePropagatingFlags = ContainsLexicalThis | ContainsLexicalSuper,
    8136            8 :     // Masks
    8137            8 :     // - Additional bitmasks
    8138            8 : }
