    8203            8 : export const enum EmitFlags {
    8204            8 :     None = 0,
    8205            8 :     SingleLine = 1 << 0,                    // The contents of this node should be emitted on a single line.
    8206            8 :     MultiLine = 1 << 1,
    8207            8 :     AdviseOnEmitNode = 1 << 2,              // The printer should invoke the onEmitNode callback when printing this node.
    8208            8 :     NoSubstitution = 1 << 3,                // Disables further substitution of an expression.
    8209            8 :     CapturesThis = 1 << 4,                  // The function captures a lexical `this`
    8210            8 :     NoLeadingSourceMap = 1 << 5,            // Do not emit a leading source map location for this node.
    8211            8 :     NoTrailingSourceMap = 1 << 6,           // Do not emit a trailing source map location for this node.
    8212            8 :     NoSourceMap = NoLeadingSourceMap | NoTrailingSourceMap, // Do not emit a source map location for this node.
    8213            8 :     NoNestedSourceMaps = 1 << 7,            // Do not emit source map locations for children of this node.
    8214            8 :     NoTokenLeadingSourceMaps = 1 << 8,      // Do not emit leading source map location for token nodes.
    8215            8 :     NoTokenTrailingSourceMaps = 1 << 9,     // Do not emit trailing source map location for token nodes.
    8216            8 :     NoTokenSourceMaps = NoTokenLeadingSourceMaps | NoTokenTrailingSourceMaps, // Do not emit source map locations for tokens of this node.
    8217            8 :     NoLeadingComments = 1 << 10,            // Do not emit leading comments for this node.
    8218            8 :     NoTrailingComments = 1 << 11,           // Do not emit trailing comments for this node.
    8219            8 :     NoComments = NoLeadingComments | NoTrailingComments, // Do not emit comments for this node.
    8220            8 :     NoNestedComments = 1 << 12,
    8221            8 :     HelperName = 1 << 13,                   // The Identifier refers to an *unscoped* emit helper (one that is emitted at the top of the file)
    8222            8 :     ExportName = 1 << 14,                   // Ensure an export prefix is added for an identifier that points to an exported declaration with a local name (see SymbolFlags.ExportHasLocal).
    8223            8 :     LocalName = 1 << 15,                    // Ensure an export prefix is not added for an identifier that points to an exported declaration.
    8224            8 :     InternalName = 1 << 16,                 // The name is internal to an ES5 class body function.
    8225            8 :     Indented = 1 << 17,                     // Adds an explicit extra indentation level for class and function bodies when printing (used to match old emitter).
    8226            8 :     NoIndentation = 1 << 18,                // Do not indent the node.
    8227            8 :     AsyncFunctionBody = 1 << 19,
    8228            8 :     ReuseTempVariableScope = 1 << 20,       // Reuse the existing temp variable scope during emit.
    8229            8 :     CustomPrologue = 1 << 21,               // Treat the statement as if it were a prologue directive (NOTE: Prologue directives are *not* transformed).
    8230            8 :     NoHoisting = 1 << 22,                   // Do not hoist this declaration in --module system
    8231            8 :     Iterator = 1 << 23,                     // The expression to a `yield*` should be treated as an Iterator when down-leveling, not an Iterable.
    8232            8 :     NoAsciiEscaping = 1 << 24,              // When synthesizing nodes that lack an original node or textSourceNode, we want to write the text on the node with ASCII escaping substitutions.
    8233            8 : }

    9185            8 :     /**
    9186            8 :      * Wraps an expression that cannot be an assignment target in an expression that can be.
    9187            8 :      *
    9188            8 :      * Given a `paramName` of `_a`:
    9189            8 :      * ```
    9190            8 :      * Reflect.set(obj, "x", _a)
    9191            8 :      * ```
    9192            8 :      * Becomes
    9193            8 :      * ```ts
    9194            8 :      * ({ set value(_a) { Reflect.set(obj, "x", _a); } }).value
    9195            8 :      * ```
    9196            8 :      *

    9198            8 :      * @param expression
    9199            8 :      *
    9200            8 :      * @internal
    9201            8 :      */

    9205            8 :      * Gets the internal name of a declaration. This is primarily used for declarations that can be
    9206            8 :      * referred to by name in the body of an ES5 class function body. An internal name will *never*
    9207            8 :      * be prefixed with an module or namespace export modifier like "exports." when emitted as an
    9208            8 :      * expression. An internal name will also *never* be renamed due to a collision with a block
    9209            8 :      * scoped variable.

    9502            8 : /**
    9503            8 :  * A function that accepts and possibly transforms a node.
    9504            8 :  */
    9505            8 : export type Visitor<TIn extends Node = Node, TOut extends Node | undefined = TIn | undefined> = (node: TIn) => VisitResult<TOut>;
    9506            8 : 
    9507            8 : /**
    9508            8 :  * A function that walks a node using the given visitor, lifting node arrays into single nodes,
    9509            8 :  * returning an node which satisfies the test.
    9510            8 :  *
    9511            8 :  * - If the input node is undefined, then the output is undefined.
    9512            8 :  * - If the visitor returns undefined, then the output is undefined.
    9513            8 :  * - If the output node is not undefined, then it will satisfy the test function.
    9514            8 :  * - In order to obtain a return type that is more specific than `Node`, a test
    9515            8 :  *   function _must_ be provided, and that function must be a type predicate.
    9516            8 :  *
    9517            8 :  * For the canonical implementation of this type, @see {visitNode}.
    9518            8 :  */
    9519            8 : export interface NodeVisitor {
    9520            8 :     <TIn extends Node | undefined, TVisited extends Node | undefined, TOut extends Node>(
    9521            8 :         node: TIn,
    9522            8 :         visitor: Visitor<NonNullable<TIn>, TVisited>,
    9523            8 :         test: (node: Node) => node is TOut,
    9524            8 :         lift?: (node: readonly Node[]) => Node,
    9525            8 :     ): TOut | (TIn & undefined) | (TVisited & undefined);
    9526            8 :     <TIn extends Node | undefined, TVisited extends Node | undefined>(
    9527            8 :         node: TIn,
    9528            8 :         visitor: Visitor<NonNullable<TIn>, TVisited>,
    9529            8 :         test?: (node: Node) => boolean,
    9530            8 :         lift?: (node: readonly Node[]) => Node,
    9531            8 :     ): Node | (TIn & undefined) | (TVisited & undefined);
    9532            8 : }
    9533            8 : 
    9534            8 : /**
    9535            8 :  * A function that walks a node array using the given visitor, returning an array whose contents satisfy the test.
    9536            8 :  *
    9537            8 :  * - If the input node array is undefined, the output is undefined.
    9538            8 :  * - If the visitor can return undefined, the node it visits in the array will be reused.
    9539            8 :  * - If the output node array is not undefined, then its contents will satisfy the test.
    9540            8 :  * - In order to obtain a return type that is more specific than `NodeArray<Node>`, a test
    9541            8 :  *   function _must_ be provided, and that function must be a type predicate.
    9542            8 :  *
    9543            8 :  * For the canonical implementation of this type, @see {visitNodes}.
    9544            8 :  */
    9545            8 : export interface NodesVisitor {
    9546            8 :     <TIn extends Node, TInArray extends NodeArray<TIn> | undefined, TOut extends Node>(
    9547            8 :         nodes: TInArray,
    9548            8 :         visitor: Visitor<TIn, Node | undefined>,
    9549            8 :         test: (node: Node) => node is TOut,
    9550            8 :         start?: number,
    9551            8 :         count?: number,
    9552            8 :     ): NodeArray<TOut> | (TInArray & undefined);
    9553            8 :     <TIn extends Node, TInArray extends NodeArray<TIn> | undefined>(
    9554            8 :         nodes: TInArray,
    9555            8 :         visitor: Visitor<TIn, Node | undefined>,
    9556            8 :         test?: (node: Node) => boolean,
    9557            8 :         start?: number,
    9558            8 :         count?: number,
    9559            8 :     ): NodeArray<Node> | (TInArray & undefined);
    9560            8 : }

    9564            8 : export interface Printer {
    9565            8 :     /**
    9566            8 :      * Print a node and its subtree as-is, without any emit transformations.
    9567            8 :      * @param hint A value indicating the purpose of a node. This is primarily used to
    9568            8 :      * distinguish between an `Identifier` used in an expression position, versus an
    9569            8 :      * `Identifier` used as an `IdentifierName` as part of a declaration. For most nodes you
    9570            8 :      * should just pass `Unspecified`.
    9571            8 :      * @param node The node to print. The node and its subtree are printed as-is, without any
    9572            8 :      * emit transformations.
    9573            8 :      * @param sourceFile A source file that provides context for the node. The source text of
    9574            8 :      * the file is used to emit the original source content for literals and identifiers, while
    9575            8 :      * the identifiers of the source file are used when generating unique names to avoid
    9576            8 :      * collisions.
    9577            8 :      */
    9578            8 :     printNode(hint: EmitHint, node: Node, sourceFile: SourceFile): string;

    9582            8 :     printList<T extends Node>(format: ListFormat, list: NodeArray<T>, sourceFile: SourceFile): string;
    9583            8 :     /**

    9585            8 :      */
    9586            8 :     printFile(sourceFile: SourceFile): string;
    9587            8 :     /**
    9588            8 :      * Prints a bundle of source files as-is, without any emit transformations.
    9589            8 :      */
    9590            8 :     printBundle(bundle: Bundle): string;
    9591            8 :     /** @internal */ writeNode(hint: EmitHint, node: Node, sourceFile: SourceFile | undefined, writer: EmitTextWriter): void;
    9592            8 :     /** @internal */ writeList<T extends Node>(format: ListFormat, list: NodeArray<T> | undefined, sourceFile: SourceFile | undefined, writer: EmitTextWriter): void;

    9594            8 :     /** @internal */ writeBundle(bundle: Bundle, writer: EmitTextWriter, sourceMapGenerator: SourceMapGenerator | undefined): void;

    9892            8 : export const enum ListFormat {
    9893            8 :     None = 0,
    9894            8 : 
    9895            8 :     // Line separators
    9896            8 :     SingleLine = 0,                 // Prints the list on a single line (default).
    9897            8 :     MultiLine = 1 << 0,             // Prints the list on multiple lines.
    9898            8 :     PreserveLines = 1 << 1,         // Prints the list using line preservation if possible.
    9899            8 :     LinesMask = SingleLine | MultiLine | PreserveLines,
    9900            8 : 
    9901            8 :     // Delimiters
    9902            8 :     NotDelimited = 0,               // There is no delimiter between list items (default).
    9903            8 :     BarDelimited = 1 << 2,          // Each list item is space-and-bar (" |") delimited.
    9904            8 :     AmpersandDelimited = 1 << 3,    // Each list item is space-and-ampersand (" &") delimited.
    9905            8 :     CommaDelimited = 1 << 4,        // Each list item is comma (",") delimited.
    9906            8 :     AsteriskDelimited = 1 << 5,     // Each list item is asterisk ("\n *") delimited, used with JSDoc.
    9907            8 :     DelimitersMask = BarDelimited | AmpersandDelimited | CommaDelimited | AsteriskDelimited,
    9908            8 : 
    9909            8 :     AllowTrailingComma = 1 << 6,    // Write a trailing comma (",") if present.
    9910            8 : 
    9911            8 :     // Whitespace
    9912            8 :     Indented = 1 << 7,              // The list should be indented.
    9913            8 :     SpaceBetweenBraces = 1 << 8,    // Inserts a space after the opening brace and before the closing brace.
    9914            8 :     SpaceBetweenSiblings = 1 << 9,  // Inserts a space between each sibling node.
    9915            8 : 
    9916            8 :     // Brackets/Braces
    9917            8 :     Braces = 1 << 10,                // The list is surrounded by "{" and "}".
    9918            8 :     Parenthesis = 1 << 11,          // The list is surrounded by "(" and ")".
    9919            8 :     AngleBrackets = 1 << 12,        // The list is surrounded by "<" and ">".
    9920            8 :     SquareBrackets = 1 << 13,       // The list is surrounded by "[" and "]".
    9921            8 :     BracketsMask = Braces | Parenthesis | AngleBrackets | SquareBrackets,
    9922            8 : 
    9923            8 :     OptionalIfUndefined = 1 << 14,  // Do not emit brackets if the list is undefined.
    9924            8 :     OptionalIfEmpty = 1 << 15,      // Do not emit brackets if the list is empty.
    9925            8 :     Optional = OptionalIfUndefined | OptionalIfEmpty,
    9926            8 : 
    9927            8 :     // Other
    9928            8 :     PreferNewLine = 1 << 16,        // Prefer adding a LineTerminator between synthesized nodes.
    9929            8 :     NoTrailingNewLine = 1 << 17,    // Do not emit a trailing NewLine for a MultiLine list.
    9930            8 :     NoInterveningComments = 1 << 18, // Do not emit comments between each node
    9931            8 :     NoSpaceIfEmpty = 1 << 19,       // If the literal is empty, do not add spaces between braces.
    9932            8 :     SingleElement = 1 << 20,
    9933            8 :     SpaceAfterList = 1 << 21,       // Add space after list
    9934            8 : 
    9935            8 :     // Precomputed Formats
    9936            8 :     Modifiers = SingleLine | SpaceBetweenSiblings | NoInterveningComments | SpaceAfterList,
    9937            8 :     HeritageClauses = SingleLine | SpaceBetweenSiblings,
    9938            8 :     SingleLineTypeLiteralMembers = SingleLine | SpaceBetweenBraces | SpaceBetweenSiblings,
    9939            8 :     MultiLineTypeLiteralMembers = MultiLine | Indented | OptionalIfEmpty,
    9940            8 : 
    9941            8 :     SingleLineTupleTypeElements = CommaDelimited | SpaceBetweenSiblings | SingleLine,
    9942            8 :     MultiLineTupleTypeElements = CommaDelimited | Indented | SpaceBetweenSiblings | MultiLine,
    9943            8 :     UnionTypeConstituents = BarDelimited | SpaceBetweenSiblings | SingleLine,
    9944            8 :     IntersectionTypeConstituents = AmpersandDelimited | SpaceBetweenSiblings | SingleLine,
    9945            8 :     ObjectBindingPatternElements = SingleLine | AllowTrailingComma | SpaceBetweenBraces | CommaDelimited | SpaceBetweenSiblings | NoSpaceIfEmpty,
    9946            8 :     ArrayBindingPatternElements = SingleLine | AllowTrailingComma | CommaDelimited | SpaceBetweenSiblings | NoSpaceIfEmpty,
    9947            8 :     ObjectLiteralExpressionProperties = PreserveLines | CommaDelimited | SpaceBetweenSiblings | SpaceBetweenBraces | Indented | Braces | NoSpaceIfEmpty,
    9948            8 :     ImportAttributes = PreserveLines | CommaDelimited | SpaceBetweenSiblings | SpaceBetweenBraces | Indented | Braces | NoSpaceIfEmpty,
    9949            8 :     /** @deprecated */ ImportClauseEntries = ImportAttributes,
    9950            8 :     ArrayLiteralExpressionElements = PreserveLines | CommaDelimited | SpaceBetweenSiblings | AllowTrailingComma | Indented | SquareBrackets,
    9951            8 :     CommaListElements = CommaDelimited | SpaceBetweenSiblings | SingleLine,

    9957            8 :     VariableDeclarationList = CommaDelimited | SpaceBetweenSiblings | SingleLine,
    9958            8 :     SingleLineFunctionBodyStatements = SingleLine | SpaceBetweenSiblings | SpaceBetweenBraces,
    9959            8 :     MultiLineFunctionBodyStatements = MultiLine,
    9960            8 :     ClassHeritageClauses = SingleLine,
    9961            8 :     ClassMembers = Indented | MultiLine,

    9963            8 :     EnumMembers = CommaDelimited | Indented | MultiLine,

    9966            8 :     JsxElementOrFragmentChildren = SingleLine | NoInterveningComments,

   10068            8 : export const enum JSDocParsingMode {

   10070            1 :      * Always parse JSDoc comments and include them in the AST.
   10071            1 :      *
   10072            1 :      * This is the default if no mode is provided.
   10073            1 :      */
   10074            1 :     ParseAll,
   10075            1 :     /**
   10076            1 :      * Never parse JSDoc comments, mo matter the file type.
   10077            1 :      */
   10078            1 :     ParseNone,
   10079            1 :     /**
   10080            1 :      * Parse only JSDoc comments which are needed to provide correct type errors.
   10081            1 :      *
   10082            1 :      * This will always parse JSDoc in non-TS files, but only parse JSDoc comments
   10083            1 :      * containing `@see` and `@link` in TS files.
   10084            1 :      */
   10085            1 :     ParseForTypeErrors,
   10086            1 :     /**
   10087            1 :      * Parse only JSDoc comments which are needed to provide correct type info.
   10088            1 :      *
   10089            1 :      * This will always parse JSDoc in non-TS files, but never in TS files.
   10090            1 :      *
   10091            1 :      * Note: Do not use this mode if you require accurate type errors; use {@link ParseForTypeErrors} instead.
   10092            1 :      */
   10093            1 :     ParseForTypeInfo,
   10094            1 : }

   10236            1 :      * for the sake of consistent sorting. Use `"auto"` to use the detected UI locale.
   10237            1 :      *
   10238            1 :      * This preference is ignored if {@link organizeImportsCollation} is not `"unicode"`.
   10239            1 :      *
   10240            1 :      * Default: `"en"`
   10241            1 :      */
   10242            1 :     readonly organizeImportsLocale?: string;
   10243            1 :     /**
   10244            1 :      * Indicates whether numeric collation should be used for digit sequences in strings. When `true`, will collate
   10245            1 :      * strings such that `a1z < a2z < a100z`. When `false`, will collate strings such that `a1z < a100z < a2z`.
   10246            1 :      *
   10247            1 :      * This preference is ignored if {@link organizeImportsCollation} is not `"unicode"`.
   10248            1 :      *
   10249            1 :      * Default: `false`
   10250            1 :      */
   10251            1 :     readonly organizeImportsNumericCollation?: boolean;
